At the beginning of each turn the game reports the directions that the player can go in.
Directions are listed in the order of north, south, east, west.

script
put player in cavern 1
enter command Rest
check message You can go south and east from here. was printed [false] expected [true]
 
enter command East
check message You can go east and west from here. was printed [false] expected [true]
 
enter command East
check message You can go south and west from here. was printed [false] expected [true]
 
enter command South
check message You can go north and south from here. was printed [false] expected [true]
 
enter command South
check message You can go north and west from here. was printed [false] expected [true]
 
enter command West
check message You can go east and west from here. was printed [false] expected [true]
 
enter command West
check message You can go north and east from here. was printed [false] expected [true]
 
enter command North
check message You can go north and south from here. was printed [false] expected [true]
 
  ''Now clear the map''
clear map
